{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"405e2759-d8c2-4bef-96f6-04aa1e23b561","content":"With **MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0**, the migration is straightforward. In your project file:\n\n**Remove** (or set to `false`):\n```xml\n<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n```\n\nThat's the key change — MSTest.Sdk **3.8.0 already defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform**, so removing `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` (or flipping it to `false`) activates it automatically.\n\n### What else to be aware of:\n\n1. **CLI change** — run tests with:\n   ```\n   dotnet run -- --help        # see new CLI options\n   dotnet test                 # still works, but delegates differently\n   ```\n\n2. **Remove legacy references** (if present):\n   - `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`\n   - `MSTest.TestAdapter`\n   - `MSTest.TestFramework`\n   \n   These are unnecessary with MSTest.Sdk and can cause conflicts.\n\n3. **`.runsettings` files** — most settings still work, but some VSTest-specific options (e.g., custom test host parameters) may need adjustment.\n\n4. **CI pipelines** — if you use `dotnet test --logger trx`, it still works. But review any VSTest-specific logger/adapter flags.\n\n### Minimal diff:\n```diff\n <Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n-    <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n </Project>\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ad6ca351-c666-40ea-bf74-685ec8120b0f","outputTokens":396,"requestId":"0C0A:20FE47:224A8C:282574:69F00569"},"id":"9cae5df0-e147-47fe-a3b9-7bf7bab826b6","timestamp":"2026-04-28T00:55:15.146Z","parentId":"ca810540-bd46-40c0-9932-261d9cd686a0"}
